"Soden B.J., Wetherald R.T., Stenchikov G.L., Robock A.","Global cooling after the eruption of Mount Pinatubo: A test of climate feedback by water vapor",2002,"Science","296","5568",,"727","730",,,10.1126/science.296.5568.727,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0037177582&partnerID=40&md5=b11ae79766eb9ae21ef37486dcd6d18c","Geophys. Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, Natl. Oceanic and Atmosph. Admin., Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08542, United States","Soden, B.J., Geophys. Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, Natl. Oceanic and Atmosph. Admin., Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08542, United States; Wetherald, R.T., Geophys. Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, Natl. Oceanic and Atmosph. Admin., Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08542, United States; Stenchikov, G.L., Geophys. Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, Natl. Oceanic and Atmosph. Admin., Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08542, United States; Robock, A., Geophys. Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, Natl. Oceanic and Atmosph. Admin., Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08542, United States","The sensitivity of Earth's climate to an external radiative forcing depends critically on the response of water vapor. We use the global cooling and drying of the atmosphere that was observed after the eruption of Mount Pinatubo to test model predictions of the climate feedback from water vapor. Here, we first highlight the success of the model in reproducing the observed drying after the volcanic eruption. Then, by comparing model simulations with and without water vapor feedback, we demonstrate the importance of the atmospheric drying in amplifying the temperature change and show that, without the strong positive feedback from water vapor, the model is unable to reproduce the observed cooling. These results provide quantitative evidence of the reliability of water vapor feedback in current climate models, which is crucial to their use for global warming projections.",,"Computer simulation; Global warming; Mathematical models; Vapors; Volcanoes; Global cooling; Climatology; climate feedback; climate modeling; cooling; volcanic eruption; water vapor; article; climate change; cooling; environmental temperature; feedback system; global climate; greenhouse effect; prediction; priority journal; volcano; water vapor; Philippines; Pinatubo",,,,,,"Kiehl, J., Trenberth, K., (1997) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 78, p. 197; Cubasch, U., Cess, R., (1990) Climate Change: The IPCC Scientific Assessment, , J. T. Houghton et al., Eds. (Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge); Wetherald, R., Manabe, S., (1988) J. Atmos. Sci., 45, p. 1397; Cess, R., (1989) J. Geophys. Res., 95, p. 16601; Held, I., Soden, B., (2000) Annu. Rev. Energy Environ., 25, p. 441; Lindzen, R., (1990) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 71, p. 288; Dickinson, R.E., (1996) Climate Change 1995: The Science of Climate Change, , J. T. Houghton et al., Eds. (Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge); Raval, A., Ramathan, V., (1989) Nature, 342, p. 758; Wentz, F., Schabel, M., (2000) Nature, 403, p. 414; Rind, D., (1991) Nature, 349, p. 500; Del Genio, A., Kovari, W., Mao-Sung, Y., (1994) Geophys. Res. Lett., 21, p. 2701; Soden, B., (1997) J. Clim., 10, p. 1050; Bony, S., Duvel, J., Le Treut, H., (1995) Clim. Dyn., 11, p. 307; Lau, K., Ho, C., Chou, M., (1996) Geophys Res. Lett., 23, p. 2971; Inamdar, A., Ramanthan, V., (1998) J. Geophys. Res., 103, p. 32177; Franklin, B., (1784) Manchester Literary and Philosophical Society Memoirs and Proceedings, 2, p. 122. , Reprinted in Weatherwise, 35, 262 (1982); Robock, A., (2000) Rev. Geophys., 38, p. 191; Hansen, J., Lacis, A., Ruedy, R., Sato, M., (1992) Geophys. Res. Lett., 19, p. 215; Kirchner, I., (1999) J. Geophys. Res., 104, p. 19039; Stowe, L., Carey, R., Pellegrino, P., (1992) Geophys. Res. Lett., 19, p. 159; Trepte, C., Veiga, R., McCormick, M., (1993) J. Geophys. Res., 98, p. 18563; Minnis, P., (1993) Science, 259, p. 1411; Robock, A., Mao, J., (1992) J. Clim., 8, p. 1086; Parker, D., Wilson, H., Christy, J., Folland, C., (